</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[189,1399,450,582]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,627,450,477]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indistincta" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,304,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[324,481,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Floccocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[500,627,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">indistincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[637,731,451,477]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
agrees with the other members of the subgenus in the following characters: a broad, densely pilose body, antennal pits separated, wing infuscated, eye pilose, and scutum without strong bristles. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[612,905,521,547]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indistincta" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[612,724,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[742,764,521,546]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[781,905,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">indistincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[913,1004,521,547]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1160,1399,521,547]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[1160,1187,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1204,1227,521,546]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1244,1399,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,280,556,582]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[336,489,556,582]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vellea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[336,363,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[380,402,556,581]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[419,489,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">vellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[496,587,556,582]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
for distinguishing characters see under 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1054,1291,556,582]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[1054,1081,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1098,1120,556,581]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1136,1291,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1299,1389,556,582]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="60.[189,324,621,647]" box="[189,324,621,647]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,621,647]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,621,647]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[189,1398,667,729]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[631,766,667,693]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">indistinctus</emphasis>
’, and refers to the fact that the species is obscure (hard to distinguish from morphologically similar species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
